<TITLE> Iraq says Basra handover to take place on Sunday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 BASRA, Iraq, Dec 12 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Iraqi forces will take responsibility for security in the last British-controlled province in four days despite a major car bomb attack in a neighbouring province, the Iraqi government said on Wednesday. The first official announcement of the date for Britain to hand over responsibility for Basra province came hours after car bombs in neighbouring Maysan province killed about 40 people and wounded more than 125. "(The bombing) has nothing to do with Basra. The handover will go ahead on the 16th of this month. The quality of the forces in Basra is excellent," government spokesman Ali al-Dabbagh said at a conference on development in Bas
